JOHANNESBURG - Musical prodigy Daniel 'Danno' Peterson is off to the US to receive the prestigious Barack Obama Lifetime Achievement Award.The 14-year-old Peterson has already made history by becoming one of South Africa's youngest music graduates, having attained a degree in music at the University of the Western Cape in 2014.Peterson is also the youngest Yamaha-endorsed drummer.Fondly known as Danno, he will receive his award on Saturday from former US president Barack Obama.*Click on the above video to see Peterson chat to eNCA about his excitement at being nominated for such a distinguished award. Click on the below video to see Daniel at a much younger age.eNCA